{{Primary sources|date=December 2007}} {{Infobox journal | cover = | discipline = [[Systems biology]] | abbreviation = BMC Syst. Biol. | website = http://www.biomedcentral.com/bmcsystbiol/ | publisher = [[BioMed Central]] | country = | ISSN = 1752-0509 | OCLC = 76922333 | history = 2007–present | frequency = Upon publication | openaccess = Yes | impact = 2.303<ref>[https://bmcsystbiol.biomedcentral.com/about BMC Systems Biology About page], retrieved 23 July 2017. Secondary validation from [http://www.scijournal.org/impact-factor-of-BMC-SYST-BIOL.shtml International Scientific Institute (ISI)]</ref> | impact-year = 2016 }} '''''BMC Systems Biology''''' is an [[Open access (publishing)|open access]] [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] that covers research in [[systems biology]]. Filling a gap in what was a new research field, the journal was established in 2007 and is published by [[BioMed Central]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hodgkinson|first=Matt J.|last2=Webb|first2=Penelope A.|date=2007-09-04|title=A system for success: BMC Systems Biology, a new open access journal|url=https://doi.org/10.1186/1752-0509-1-41|journal=BMC Systems Biology|volume=1|pages=41|doi=10.1186/1752-0509-1-41|issn=1752-0509|pmc=1976322|pmid=17784938}}</ref> Part of the [[BMC series|BMC Series]] of journals, it has a broad scope covering the engineering of biological systems, network modelling, quantitative analyses, integration of different levels of information and [[synthetic biology]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bmcsystbiol.biomedcentral.com/about|title=BMC Systems Biology|website=BMC Systems Biology|language=en|access-date=2017-07-23}}</ref>
